    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fiberboard that is typically made of wood fibers that are acquired by breaking down scrap remnants of hardwood or softwood; distinguished from low-density fiberboard and high-density fiberboard by density of fiber and strength.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
